It is the 41st combination in the Sexagenary cycle, following {{ill|癸卯|ja|癸卯|12=draft}} and preceding {{ill|乙巳|ja|乙巳|12=draft}}. In {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft}}, {{ill|甲|ja|十干|12=draft}} represents the {{ill|Yang|ja|陽|12=draft}} aspect of {{ill|Wood|ja|木|12=draft}}, while {{ill|辰|ja|十二支|12=draft}} represents the Yang aspect of {{ill|Earth|ja|土|12=draft}}. This combination is classified as an instance of {{ill|Mutual Controlling (Wood Controls Earth)|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=相剋|12=draft}}.
